The dict protocol, and dict.org in particular, provides easy access to Webster&#x27;s 1913 as well as other dictionaries.<p>I normally use Webster&#x27;s 1913 from the command line, since I usually have a terminal in front of me. I keep this in my .zshrc:<p><pre><code>    function dict () {
        if [[ $1 == (d|m) ]]; then
                curl dict://dict.org/$1:$2 | $PAGER
        else
            echo &#x27;Unknown command. Use (d)efine or (m)atch.&#x27;
        fi
    }
</code></pre>
That allows me to issue queries such as `dict d example` to define &quot;example&quot;, or `dict m exampel` to figure out how &quot;example&quot; ought to be spelled.
